We chiefly investigated the facial depression of males. Optical pictures show a yellow cuticular surface, most probably membranous, overlaid by the darker sclerotized external cuticle of face (
Figure 2a
). The STEM images depict more precisely the facial depression and the invagination of its lateral walls (
Figure 1c
). They also show the crown of setae surrounding the depression (
Figure 1b
). In female, the evenly setose face shows only a shallow glabrous central concavity at its center (
Figure 4b
).

